Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.49,0:01:29.99,Show_Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,That {\c&H471E13&}Time {\c&HCD9612&}I Got {\c&H471E13&}Reincarnated {\c&HCD9612&}as a {\c&H7E4F0A&}Slime
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.35,0:01:33.99,Flashback,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing \Nto my bestie's subordinate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.33,0:01:42.04,Ep_Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1487,561)}Episode 18: Evil Creeps Closer
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.96,0:01:49.15,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! She'll pay for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.49,0:01:53.85,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Who does she think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.85,0:01:56.06,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Phobio the Black Leopard Fang!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.48,0:02:00.09,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,With the Demon Lord Milim in the \Npicture, it's beyond our control.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.44,0:02:02.73,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Even for the Demon Lord Carrion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.89,0:02:04.08,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.08,0:02:07.35,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Carrion wouldn't have \Nhumiliated himself like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.90,0:02:09.95,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I just wasn't good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.75,0:02:16.00,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,But my pride won't allow \Nme to go back empty-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.44,0:02:21.29,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Those guys built a town all on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.93,0:02:24.44,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I saw them as no more than lowly monsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.67,0:02:27.70,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,but they have skills and \Ntechniques that even we lack.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.32,0:02:29.75,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,That's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.75,0:02:31.87,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of ordering them to serve us,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.87,0:02:35.56,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to see Eurazania establish \Ndiplomatic relations with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.86,0:02:39.10,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Even if the Demon Lord \NMilim hadn't been involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.55,0:02:41.69,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I handled that all wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.17,0:02:46.94,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't have gained their trust by just \Ntaking over without giving them a say.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.78,0:02:49.33,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,But it's too late now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.80,0:02:53.90,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,My wounds may heal, but this \Nhumiliation will never fade.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.90,0:02:56.57,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I want to take revenge somehow,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.57,0:02:59.25,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,so I won't cause trouble for Lord Carrion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.65,0:03:03.54,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,That's easy to say, but \Nrevenge isn't realistic...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.54,0:03:06.67,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I know that! I know in my \Nhead that it won't work!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.55,0:03:11.34,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I just can't rationalize this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.83,0:03:17.01,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.29,0:03:30.11,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, how well I understand that \Nvexation you must be feeling!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.93,0:03:32.87,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Greetings, fine people!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.87,0:03:35.49,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Footman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.95,0:03:37.12,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Footman?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.29,0:03:39.54,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,I am a member of the \NModerate Harlequin Alliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.54,0:03:43.43,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,the one they call Footman the Angry Pierrot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.90,0:03:45.83,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasure to make your acquaintance!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.68,0:03:50.09,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Now, please don't be so guarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.97,0:03:54.30,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Tear, and I'm not your enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.76,0:03:55.98,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.33,0:04:03.48,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I was summoned here \Nby your anger and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.92,0:04:05.91,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Anger and hatred?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.45,0:04:09.28,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,I sensed some choice waves of anger, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.49,0:04:14.69,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell me what has angered you so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.58,0:04:18.77,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I can be of some help to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.45,0:04:26.15,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Phobio, there is no need \Nto listen to these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.15,0:04:27.67,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,May I remove them from your presence?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.87,0:04:32.71,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,We are the Beast King's Beastketeers, \Nserving the Demon Lord Carrion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.71,0:04:36.19,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Do you honestly think you wandering \Nmajin are any match for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.65,0:04:39.09,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,You desire power, do you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.09,0:04:43.13,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,We have it... power akin \Nto none you've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.19,0:04:46.83,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, however, it comes with great risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.83,0:04:49.93,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,But should you triumph over that risk,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:52.15,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,the power you stand to gain is immense.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.17,0:04:54.03,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.38,0:04:55.28,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Phobio!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:04:58.74,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,You want to defeat the \NDemon Lord Milim, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.74,0:05:02.16,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Then you just need to become \Na Demon Lord yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.31,0:05:04.54,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Demon... Lord?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.77,0:05:14.17,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,A Demon Lord? You think you can \Nfool me with nonsense like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.46,0:05:15.30,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Charybdis.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.98,0:05:21.82,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Have you heard of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.39,0:05:24.93,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say... Charybdis?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.69,0:05:30.72,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, if you had the evil power \Nof that gigantic beast-fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.72,0:05:33.23,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,you'd be a Demon Lord's equal...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.23,0:05:36.03,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,But if you don't want it, \Nwe'll just go find someone who does!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.01,0:05:39.57,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.96,0:05:42.49,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,What a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.77,0:05:43.58,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.58,0:05:47.73,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Phobio, you mustn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.13,0:05:50.95,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't liked any of this from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.95,0:05:55.26,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Why was a useless Orc Lord \Nchosen to be a Demon Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.44,0:05:56.82,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,That's bull!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.82,0:06:00.35,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,If they need a new Demon Lord, I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.64,0:06:05.35,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get stronger! Then even Lord \NCarrion will forgive me with a smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.35,0:06:06.84,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Phobio...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.24,0:06:08.48,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me more!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.73,0:06:11.87,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! I knew the great \NSir Phobio would understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.87,0:06:16.61,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course! There is none more \Nsuited than you to be a Demon Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.61,0:06:20.36,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,It's just wrong for anyone who isn't \Nstrong to be a Demon Lord, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.36,0:06:22.07,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I feel, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.07,0:06:24.74,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,And as far as that goes, \Nyou're perfect for the job!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.62,0:06:31.93,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,What do you two stand to gain from this deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.42,0:06:33.66,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,What are you after?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.66,0:06:37.35,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,We just want you to give us special \Ntreatment once you become a Demon Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.35,0:06:40.43,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like you to do a few favors for us, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:46.45,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot subdue Charybdis \Non our own, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.45,0:06:49.44,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,We managed to find the place \Nwhere it's been sealed away,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.44,0:06:51.81,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,but as it is now, we're just \Nsitting on a gold mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.96,0:06:55.19,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,And we just happened to find \Nyou at the perfect time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.19,0:06:57.57,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.57,0:07:01.95,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no telling whether \NI can subdue Charybdis or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.80,0:07:06.82,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,If anyone can do it, \Nit's you, great Sir Phobio!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.82,0:07:08.41,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.39,0:07:11.30,Italics,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,So when I become a Demon Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.30,0:07:15.66,Italics,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,they want to be the ones credited \Nfor helping me the most?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.21,0:07:21.14,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I accept your offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.25,0:07:27.47,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,You three can go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.64,0:07:29.04,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Phobio!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.04,0:07:31.10,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Report on everything that has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.41,0:07:32.39,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,But..
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.87,0:07:35.42,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I can't cause trouble for Lord Carrion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.42,0:07:39.40,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him I'm resigning my position in the \NBeastketeers and leaving the service.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.18,0:07:42.71,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for all you've done for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:44.66,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Phobio...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.09,0:07:49.91,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I will become carnage itself and force the \NDemon Lord Milim to acknowledge my power.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.87,0:07:53.17,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.97,0:07:56.40,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,I will report to Lord Carrion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.40,0:07:59.66,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,But the extent of Charybdis's \Npower is unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.66,0:08:01.88,Main,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Please be extremely careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.82,0:08:13.21,Italics,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Phobio is not a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.64,0:08:16.33,Italics,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,Even if Charybdis really is out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.33,0:08:18.51,Italics,Enrio,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he can subdue it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.72,0:08:25.91,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let us be on our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.55,0:08:30.53,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. If my power and that \Nof Charybdis can be combined,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.53,0:08:35.29,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I bet I can turn Demon Lord Milim's \Nannoying face into a sobbing mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.70,0:08:37.80,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,That's the spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.80,0:08:40.36,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! I'll be cheering you on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.45,0:08:54.69,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think of that?! I won!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.69,0:08:57.56,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,I can stay underwater longer than you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.76,0:08:59.86,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was I who won.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.02,0:09:03.94,Main,Shuna,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was only by a \Nslight margin, but I won.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:07.85,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,No fair refusing to admit \Ndefeat, Shion and Shuna!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.85,0:09:11.45,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then, we'll do it again! \NLet's settle the score!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.74,0:09:13.79,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. One more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.79,0:09:18.12,Main,Shuna,0000,0000,0000,,It's really not a good idea to stay \Nunderwater in the bath, but let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.12,0:09:19.67,Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Ready... go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.14,0:09:24.22,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like they're having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.22,0:09:26.94,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should've gone to that side.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.94,0:09:28.22,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Over here is just...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.07,0:09:30.29,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,an old dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.52,0:09:34.85,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, how long do you intend \Nto stay in this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.85,0:09:37.94,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still not convinced \Nthat we're harmless?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.13,0:09:40.62,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.62,0:09:44.32,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,My suspicion of you is long gone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.49,0:09:46.02,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Then why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.02,0:09:50.28,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this place is just so comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.95,0:09:53.17,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't had a real break in so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.17,0:09:56.66,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,I felt it would be a good \Nthing to slow down and relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.91,0:09:58.90,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, man...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.90,0:10:05.03,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,"I will see for myself whether or not \Nyou are truly an ally of Humans."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.47,0:10:08.05,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,After you sounded so cool saying that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.91,0:10:10.30,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,He's not even listening!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.49,0:10:11.15,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.15,0:10:11.84,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.21,0:10:14.93,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on with Youm \Nand his guys, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.26,0:10:19.56,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You promised to help make them look \Nlike the heros in our place!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.92,0:10:21.06,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.06,0:10:22.86,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,"Ah" isn't an answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.86,0:10:25.03,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Those guys already left, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.38,0:10:28.65,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,They went to build a reputation \Nas heros everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.94,0:10:30.93,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,That won't be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.30,0:10:33.63,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,I've already finished setting things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.63,0:10:34.79,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You have?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.79,0:10:36.12,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.12,0:10:40.17,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,I've already laid the groundwork \Nfor spreading the word that they're
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.17,0:10:42.04,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,the heros who defeated the Orc Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.30,0:10:47.38,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,and for spreading the rumor \Nthat you and your people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.38,0:10:49.57,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,are the harmless monsters who helped them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.94,0:10:53.26,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Well, good, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.01,0:10:57.15,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,He may be taking it easy, \Nbut I guess he's done his part.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.65,0:11:00.19,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll be heading back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.45,0:11:01.73,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I almost forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.73,0:11:06.20,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to build a road from \Nhere to your Kingdom of Blumund.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.20,0:11:06.94,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.35,0:11:09.53,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Er... Wha? Oh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.72,0:11:11.91,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,I'd certainly appreciate that,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.91,0:11:14.16,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,but that would be a national \Nundertaking on a huge scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.59,0:11:16.09,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,The budget would be immense.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.09,0:11:17.54,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly, Fuze-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.68,0:11:19.38,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.38,0:11:23.92,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, hearing you call me \Nthat makes me feel uneasy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.14,0:11:26.53,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about that, Fuze-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.98,0:11:30.17,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Having a road would make it easier \Nfor us to do business, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.50,0:11:33.89,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, we'll handle the physical work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.46,0:11:35.51,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.51,0:11:36.68,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,However?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.39,0:11:41.00,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I want to sell our specially-made \Ngoods to other countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.00,0:11:44.51,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,so I'd like you to introduce me to someone \Nwho can give all the advice I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.01,0:11:47.78,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. That's a simple matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.78,0:11:49.01,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Good, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.79,0:11:54.44,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should go over there after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.34,0:11:59.39,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,It's in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.39,0:12:00.45,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.02,0:12:05.74,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't been revived yet, but its \Nthirst for destruction is pouring out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.62,0:12:10.11,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Such emotions are our \Nabsolute favorite treat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.11,0:12:12.23,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,That is how we were able to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.01,0:12:16.92,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,You're right... I can feel \Nsomething bizarre in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.54,0:12:19.83,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Charybdis...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.48,0:12:25.85,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Under normal circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.85,0:12:28.50,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,reviving Charybdis would \Nrequire many corpses.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.50,0:12:29.36,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Corpses?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.66,0:12:33.65,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Charybdis is a type of spiritual lifeform.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.65,0:12:36.41,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,In order to use its power in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.41,0:12:39.16,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,one must give it a physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.37,0:12:41.50,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I get it. And?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.98,0:12:44.04,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Your role in all this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.37,0:12:48.88,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, are you saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.40,0:12:54.22,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,By "subdue," we mean that you \Ntake Charybdis into your body
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.46,0:12:58.09,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,and unite with it as one being!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.96,0:13:00.62,Main,Phobo,0000,0000,0000,,Into my body?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.12,0:13:03.17,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,If you want out, now's your chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.63,0:13:04.69,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.69,0:13:05.48,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.78,0:13:09.23,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,This seal might not hold out much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.32,0:13:12.40,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,And if it doesn't, then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.64,0:13:16.07,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,It would eventually revive \Non its own... I guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.07,0:13:17.86,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,But it needs corpses, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.86,0:13:20.34,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but even though it's sealed,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.34,0:13:25.54,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it could acquire the corpses \Nnecessary for revival on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.99,0:13:29.56,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,And if it does, we might just drop dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.56,0:13:30.92,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.45,0:13:35.17,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,If it revives on its own, \Nit'll be uncontrollable,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.35,0:13:40.07,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,and with an untainted will to destroy, \Nit won't take orders from anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.79,0:13:43.46,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,So we need to break the seal \Nbefore it revives itself
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.46,0:13:46.27,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,and take its power for ourselves first?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.41,0:13:47.33,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.33,0:13:49.80,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah! Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.80,0:13:51.12,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Very perceptive!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.73,0:13:52.73,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.17,0:13:56.69,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make the power of Charybdis my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.00,0:14:06.44,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.05,0:14:10.04,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,I'll subdue Charybdis within my own body
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:14.33,Main,Phobio,0000,0000,0000,,and show that impertinent Demon Lord Milim!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.86,0:14:20.36,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he went in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.36,0:14:21.75,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,He sure did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.75,0:14:26.11,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,He is truly a minion of Carrion's, \Nwith muscles for brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.11,0:14:28.07,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that was easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.99,0:14:32.69,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,Is this job completed now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.11,0:14:39.01,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Clayman only told me to revive \NCharybdis and send it Milim's way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.01,0:14:39.57,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.50,0:14:44.89,Main,Tear,0000,0000,0000,,The lesser dragon corpse \Nthat I prepared is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.89,0:14:49.47,Main,Footman,0000,0000,0000,,But so long as we're prepared, \Nwe've nothing to worry about!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.76,0:14:58.54,Main,Gido,0000,0000,0000,,So heavy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.00,0:15:02.84,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Another great haul today!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.43,0:15:06.56,Main,Eren,0000,0000,0000,,Milim's truly amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.56,0:15:11.27,Main,Eren,0000,0000,0000,,She can locate monsters right \Naway, so hunting is a breeze!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.47,0:15:15.17,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Detecting monsters is a piece of cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.17,0:15:16.78,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have another feast tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.04,0:15:19.73,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, great work, great work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.73,0:15:21.91,Main,Gido,0000,0000,0000,,It was a lot of work, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.31,0:15:24.41,Main,Kaval,0000,0000,0000,,Who's up for a bath and a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.62,0:15:26.34,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,I'm up for a drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.70,0:15:29.83,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Milim!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.42,0:15:32.46,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.76,0:15:33.70,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.70,0:15:35.09,Main,Eren,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.48,0:15:36.42,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,This presence...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.09,0:15:44.53,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Treyni-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:46.97,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,No, she's not quite the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.17,0:15:49.35,Main,Gido,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's a Dryad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.35,0:15:50.99,Main,Kaval,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen one before...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.65,0:15:55.58,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,I am the Dryad Trya,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.58,0:15:57.36,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,younger sister of Treyni.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.36,0:15:59.03,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,She has a younger sister?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.03,0:16:02.67,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, anyway, what's with that \Nform and the murderous aura?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.30,0:16:05.29,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,There is an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.65,0:16:07.58,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,Calamity is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.58,0:16:08.70,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Calamity?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.58,0:16:13.37,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,A calamity-class monster, \NCharybdis, has been revived.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.65,0:16:14.87,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Charybdis?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.01,0:16:19.67,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,Its violence equals that of a Demon Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.16,0:16:24.32,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,My sisters, including Treyni, \Nhave set out to slow its progress,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.32,0:16:26.01,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,but they are no match for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.59,0:16:29.67,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,And it appears Charybdis is heading
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.15,0:16:31.56,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,for this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.56,0:16:32.18,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.93,0:16:40.16,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,Against Charybdis, the Ruler of the Skies, \Nwaging war on land is futile.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.77,0:16:43.49,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,I have come to advise you \Nto bolster your defenses
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.49,0:16:47.42,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,and prepare an airborne combat \Nforce as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:53.58,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,Charybdis was born long, long ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.09,0:16:56.76,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,and has died and revived many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.76,0:16:59.34,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,It is a violent Ruler of the Skies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.79,0:17:02.95,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,No less is expected of the child
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.31,0:17:06.84,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,of Veldora, the ruler and \Nguardian of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.11,0:17:08.85,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Veldora's child?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.17,0:17:14.85,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,Charybdis was generated from a \Ncloud of Veldora's magicules.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.68,0:17:19.37,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So does that mean Charybdis and \NI are sort of like brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.00,0:17:24.27,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so is it coming this \Nway because it's after me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.27,0:17:28.15,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it figured out that \NVeldora is inside me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.94,0:17:33.56,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,If Charybdis has revived, it is a \Nthreat greater than a Demon Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.99,0:17:38.29,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike a Demon Lord, this is not \Nan opponent we can speak with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.53,0:17:41.04,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,You might as well call it a \Nmonster with no intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.42,0:17:46.42,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,It's said that it calls shark-like \Nsummon monsters called Megalodons
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.42,0:17:50.68,Main,Vesta,0000,0000,0000,,from the spirit world to \Njoin it in its rampage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.93,0:17:54.68,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck? That sounds \Nworse than the Orc Lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.99,0:17:56.69,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,The situation could not be worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.05,0:17:59.09,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,Its summoned Megalodons have occupied
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.09,0:18:03.44,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,some lesser dragon corpses that were \Nnearby for some unknown reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.61,0:18:04.44,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.73,0:18:06.46,Main,Trya,0000,0000,0000,,They number thirteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.88,0:18:09.03,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,So there's one beast as bad as a Demon Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.03,0:18:11.95,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,and thirteen flying sharks that it summoned?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.48,0:18:14.84,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell kind of joke is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.35,0:18:17.46,Main,Shuna,0000,0000,0000,,Rimuru-sama, what shall we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.69,0:18:19.12,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do? I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.13,0:18:24.22,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you forgotten something important?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.22,0:18:26.05,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,That stupid Charybdis...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.05,0:18:28.84,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,is no match for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.20,0:18:30.76,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,I'll whoop its butt in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.94,0:18:32.72,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah! That's one way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.72,0:18:35.44,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.44,0:18:37.64,Main,Shion,0000,0000,0000,,This is our town's problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.79,0:18:40.02,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, secretary! Don't turn her down for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.18,0:18:42.69,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But I'm his besti—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.69,0:18:43.82,Main,Shuna,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.22,0:18:47.24,Main,Shuna,0000,0000,0000,,It's wrong to rely on you for everything \Njust because you're a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.88,0:18:50.60,Main,Shuna,0000,0000,0000,,When Rimuru-sama is in \Ndesperate need of help,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:53.49,Main,Shuna,0000,0000,0000,,we would certainly appreciate \Nyour assistance then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.49,0:18:55.93,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I'm in pretty desperate need now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.85,0:18:59.40,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,They're right, Milim.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.40,0:19:01.38,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Just have faith in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.08,0:19:08.34,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,And I thought... I'd finally \Nget my chance to shine...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.57,0:19:11.05,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it seems like it's after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.05,0:19:13.57,Italics,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I can't rely too much on Milim.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.91,0:19:18.47,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Begin preparations to defeat Charybdis!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.72,0:19:19.73,Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.03,0:19:25.59,Main,Milim,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I wanted to show my bestie what I can do...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.62,0:19:23.26,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Defeat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.86,0:19:26.31,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.86,0:19:30.86,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,You're up against a beast that \Neven the Dryads couldn't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.60,0:19:35.12,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,We can count on backup from King Gazel, \Nsince we signed that treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.12,0:19:36.87,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just do all we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.96,0:19:39.41,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't going to run away?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.81,0:19:41.43,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,What good would that do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.43,0:19:43.77,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the strongest one in this nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.67,0:19:50.38,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,If it looks like I stand no chance, \NI'll run away and think up a new plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.38,0:19:55.18,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,but otherwise, I should see how strong \Nit is with my own eyes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.26,0:19:58.69,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.69,0:20:01.23,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,You are the leader of \Nthe monsters, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.57,0:20:06.12,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,We're not like Humans who are \Ndone for if they lose their king.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.70,0:20:08.36,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.73,0:20:13.48,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,You think much like we Humans do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.48,0:20:15.87,Main,Fuze,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to see you as a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.08,0:20:18.95,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.95,0:20:23.87,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,It might be hard to believe, \Nbut I actually used to be human.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.34,0:20:26.42,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,You know about Shizu-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.69,0:20:30.13,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'm an Otherworlder, \Njust like she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.88,0:20:32.47,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I died in my world...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.76,0:20:38.01,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,and was reborn here as a slime.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.77,0:20:40.85,Main,Eren,0000,0000,0000,,Shizu...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:47.18,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Shizu-san entrusted everything to me \Nas someone from the same homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.80,0:20:51.81,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I gained this form in exchange \Nfor inheriting her will.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.14,0:20:58.07,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go making dumb mistakes \Nin Shizu-san's form, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.83,0:21:00.16,Main,Eren,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.16,0:21:03.29,Main,Eren,0000,0000,0000,,So Rimuru really is someone we can trust!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.11,0:21:07.37,Main,Rimuru,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I made a promise to her.
